<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-971-920  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 971 920.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer-Aided Design  Nov 1989 v21 n9 p577(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer-aided modelling and simulation of mechanisms andmanipulators. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fanghella, P.; Galletti, C.; Giannotti, E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Some choices related to the design and implementation of computerprograms for the kinematic modelling and simulation of mechanismsand manipulators are discussed, including global versus modularmodelling features, numeric versus symbolic computation, andprecompiler versus interpreter implementation.andP;  Within thisframework, two original applications are presented: first, aprogram for modelling spatial single-loop robot arms that works asa precompiler of manipulators and reaches an automatic, symbolic,closed-form solution to the inverse position analysis; and second,an approach to friendly training in computer-aided mechanismdesign through hypertext.andP;  Various examples of implementations aregiven.andP;  (Reprinted by permission of the publisher.)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer-Aided DesignModelingSimulationKinematicsManipulatorsTheoretical ResearchRobotics IndustrySoftware DesignMathematical Models.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   Robot arm precompiler. (chart)Example of a robot arm and its structural data. (chart)Table of equivalent constraints. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>